  "recommendations": [
    "Maintenance category dominates at 51.3% of all work orders (4,077 of 7,953). Consider implementing preventive maintenance programs for the most common issues to reduce reactive maintenance volume.",
    "Average completion time is 17 days. With only 9.4% of work orders completed within 24 hours and 50.6% within a week, there is significant room to improve response times for high-priority items.",
    "Yellow Brick Property generates 46.8% of all work orders (3,723). A focused property condition assessment and capital improvement plan for YBP properties could significantly reduce maintenance volume.",
    "Common Areas account for 32.8% of work orders (2,611). Establishing a dedicated common area maintenance schedule could reduce reactive common area issues.",
    "There are 74 open work orders currently, with 11 aging over 90 days. Implement a weekly review process to prevent work orders from aging beyond 30 days.",
    "Turnover work orders average 12.1 days to complete (633 total, 8% of all WOs). Standardizing a turnover checklist and pre-scheduling vendors could reduce this to under 7 days.",
    "Repeat issues within 90 days are high (6,403 instances). Root-cause analysis on recurring problems would reduce callbacks and total maintenance spend.",
    "Home Depot is the #1 vendor at $1.1M in 2025-2026. Negotiating a commercial account discount or bulk pricing agreement could yield 5-10% savings.",
    "Seasonal analysis shows January has the highest volume (avg 151/mo) while May is lowest (avg 121/mo). Pre-position resources and supplies before the winter peak.",
    "HVAC Routine maintenance (195 WOs, 2.5%) has the longest avg completion at 72.2 days. Expanding preventive HVAC service could reduce emergency HVAC calls."
